="sc-fyVeKD hlsaZG pf-25_">Image by drazenphoto&nbsp;via Envato Elements</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-6682" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dQEsWe gFKonE pf-26_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-deXguC bAaQfZ"><div class="sc-feUYzb iXyfoG pf-27_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bJBfJu drQDYO pf-28_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-29_">Our power, our planet: Driving change through clean energy</h3><p class="sc-kqGpvY jemTnU pf-31_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-82cdf959-086e-4ff2-8523-72de91bdbe2f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">This Earth Day, the world unites under the theme "Our Power, Our Planet", a powerful reminder that we hold the key to our planet’s future. With climate change accelerating, communities are being called to act swiftly and collaboratively. The focus for 2025 is clear: we must transition to renewable energy, reduce our dependency on fossil fuels, and amplify the voices of those affected by environmental degradation.<br><br>Earth Day 2025 aims to inspire collective action towards tripling renewable energy production by 2030, in line with global climate goals and the Paris Agreement.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-feUYzb iXyfoG pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bJBfJu drQDYO pf-35_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-36_">Why this matters</h3><p class="sc-kqGpvY jemTnU pf-38_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f2452372-de91-4dbe-af73-d5951cbe8018"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The energy crisis is no longer just about electricity, it's about equality, health, and survival. Fossil fuel dependency continues to contribute to air pollution, climate-related disasters, and health inequalities. Yet, renewable energy offers hope, not only as a sustainable alternative but as a catalyst for economic recovery, climate resilience, and improved public health.<br><br>By switching to solar, wind, hydro, and geothermal energy sources, we reduce greenhouse gas emissions, protect ecosystems, and create green jobs, all while fostering global equity.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-41_">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-44_">The burning of fossil fuels accounts for over 75% of global greenhouse gas emissions (UN).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-46_">Air pollution causes 7 million premature deaths every year (WHO), largely due to fossil fuel emissions.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-48_">Renewables could provide 65% of the world’s electricity by 2030, with the right investment and policies.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-50_">Tripling renewable energy capacity by 2030 could reduce energy sector emissions by 80%.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-52_">How does this relate to health, social care, and education?
</h3><p class="sc-kqGpvY jemTnU pf-54_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-cef4be5a-097b-4ad5-895b-b790b74a08c3"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Professionals across regulated sectors have a vital role in achieving sustainability goals. The impact of climate change is felt most deeply in health and social care, where vulnerable populations are exposed to extreme weather, air pollution, and unstable infrastructure.
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-57_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-58_">Healthcare facilities are major energy consumers. Greener practices reduce operating costs and carbon footprints.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-60_">Social care providers often support people living in fuel poverty or areas impacted by environmental hazards.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-62_">Educational institutions are hubs for sustainability learning and can influence future generations to protect the planet.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-feUYzb iXyfoG pf-64_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bJBfJu drQDYO pf-65_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-66_">Best practices for sustainability in regulated sectors</h3><p class="sc-kqGpvY jemTnU pf-68_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-644f90d0-f9e3-436f-baf5-3fe981b8a355"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Below are the best practices for sustainability in regulated sectors.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-71_">In health and social care</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-73_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-74_">Conduct an energy audit to identify areas for carbon reduction.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-76_">Transition to low-carbon technologies (e.g., heat pumps, solar panels).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-78_">Reduce waste through digital recordkeeping and efficient use of resources.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-80_">Provide staff with climate literacy and environmental awareness training.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-82_">In education</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-84_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-85_">Promote climate education across all levels and disciplines.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-87_">Encourage energy-saving behaviours among students and staff.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-89_">Participate in green campus initiatives, including local clean-up drives or renewable installations.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-91_">In business and local government</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-93_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-94_">Develop and enforce sustainable procurement policies.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-96_">Support remote working and active transport to reduce carbon emissions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-98_">Engage in partnerships with renewable energy providers.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-feUYzb iXyfoG pf-100_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bJBfJu drQDYO pf-101_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-102_">How can you take action this Earth Day</h3><p class="sc-kqGpvY jemTnU pf-104_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-e94c64d6-448a-4759-8eb5-f26b20a6898b"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Here are five ways you and your organisation can take meaningful steps this Earth Day:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-107_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-108_">Switch to renewable energy providers where possible.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-110_">Review and update your environmental policy.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-112_">Engage your team with a “Green Hour” or sustainability workshop.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-114_">Share your journey on social media with #OurPowerOurPlanet and #EarthDay2025.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-116_">Invest in sustainability training for your staff to support long-term change.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-feUYzb iXyfoG pf-118_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bJBfJu drQDYO pf-119_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-120_">Recommendations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-epAKVu bzHUyF pf-122_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-123_">Include climate risk assessments in your compliance strategy.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-125_">Assign a sustainability lead in your workplace to champion green policies.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-127_">Monitor energy, waste, and water usage to report on environmental KPIs.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iLsJvT bAOpBE pf-129_">Embed environmental goals into your corporate social responsibility (CSR) and inspection readiness.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-feUYzb iXyfoG pf-131_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bJBfJu drQDYO pf-132_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dExXmK Xerjk pf-133_">Conclusion</h3><p class="sc-kqGpvY jemTnU pf-135_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a75420f5-b90b-4c01-8227-f3368fda251e"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Earth Day 2025 reminds us that we are not powerless in the face of the climate crisis. With the theme "Our Power, Our Planet," we are called to unite, innovate, and lead. Whether you work in healthcare, education, or business, your actions can impact systems, inspire communities, and drive the shift toward a cleaner, healthier world.<br><br>At <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">The Mandatory Training Group</span></em></a>, we empower professionals and organisations to lead on sustainability through high-quality, CPD-accredited online courses that cover environmental awareness, waste management, health and safety, infection prevention, and climate risk. These courses support regulated sectors, including health, social care, and education, in embedding sustainable practices into everyday operations.<br>
